<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="creating-requests">Creating demand requests</h2>

<p>Demand requests capture new work proposals with comprehensive information organised into sections. Each section must be completed before the request can be submitted for triage.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Request sections</h3>

<p>Demand requests are organised into the following sections:</p>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Overview</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Basic information about the demand request including title, description, and business case.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Strategic alignment</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Link to strategic objectives, mission pillars, and demonstrate strategic value.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Impact and risk</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Assess impact, identify risks, and link to risk types. Calculate predicted risk level.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Delivery planning</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Plan delivery approach, timelines, dependencies, and resource requirements.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Delivery</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Delivery details, milestones, and success criteria.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Funding and headcount</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Financial requirements, resource needs, and funding sources.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Assessment</h4>
                <p class="small mb-0">Overall assessment, recommendations, and decision support information.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating a demand request</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Demand management → Requests</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Create new request"</strong></li>
    <li>Complete each section:
        <ul>
            <li>Navigate between sections using the section navigation</li>
            <li>Each section shows completion status</li>
            <li>Required fields are clearly marked</li>
            <li>Save progress regularly</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Add contacts and assign ownership</li>
    <li>Add notes and comments as needed</li>
    <li>Once all sections are complete, submit to triage</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Demand requests can be saved as drafts and completed over time. Section completion status is tracked to help you see what still needs to be done.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="sections">Request sections detail</h2>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Overview section</h3>

<p>The overview section captures basic information about the demand request:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear, descriptive title for the request</li>
    <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of what is being requested</li>
    <li><strong>Business case:</strong> Justification and business value</li>
    <li><strong>Portfolio:</strong> Which portfolio this request belongs to</li>
    <li><strong>Tier:</strong> Governance tier (Project, Programme, Portfolio, Department, Cross-government)</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Strategic alignment section</h3>

<p>Demonstrate how the request aligns with strategic objectives:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Link to strategic objectives</li>
    <li>Link to mission pillars</li>
    <li>Describe strategic value and contribution</li>
    <li>Identify related strategic initiatives</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Impact and risk section</h3>

<p>Assess the impact and risks associated with the request:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Impact assessment:</strong> Describe the impact if delivered or not delivered</li>
    <li><strong>Risk identification:</strong> Link to risk types to calculate predicted risk level</li>
    <li><strong>Risk if not delivered:</strong> Describe consequences of not proceeding</li>
    <li><strong>Predicted risk level:</strong> Automatically calculated from linked risk types</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Delivery planning section</h3>

<p>Plan how the work will be delivered:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Delivery approach and methodology</li>
    <li>Timeline and key milestones</li>
    <li>Dependencies on other work</li>
    <li>Resource requirements</li>
    <li>Delivery risks and assumptions</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Delivery section</h3>

<p>Define what will be delivered:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Deliverables and outputs</li>
    <li>Success criteria</li>
    <li>Key milestones</li>
    <li>Acceptance criteria</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Funding and headcount section</h3>

<p>Specify financial and resource requirements:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Total funding required</li>
    <li>Funding sources</li>
    <li>Headcount requirements (permanent and MSP)</li>
    <li>Resource allocation percentages</li>
    <li>Budget breakdown</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Assessment section</h3>

<p>Provide overall assessment and recommendations:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Overall assessment summary</li>
    <li>Recommendations</li>
    <li>Decision support information</li>
    <li>Alternative options considered</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="triage">Triage process</h2>

<p>Triage meetings review demand requests and make decisions about whether to proceed, defer, or reject them.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Submitting to triage</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Complete all required sections of the demand request</li>
    <li>Navigate to the demand request detail view</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Submit to triage"</strong></li>
    <li>Select the triage meeting</li>
    <li>Add any triage notes or context</li>
    <li>Submit the request</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Triage meetings</h3>

<p>Triage meetings are scheduled governance meetings where demand requests are reviewed:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Create triage meetings with dates and attendees</li>
    <li>View all requests submitted to a specific meeting</li>
    <li>Review requests during the meeting</li>
    <li>Record decisions and outcomes</li>
    <li>Track triage meeting history</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Triage decisions</h3>

<p>During triage, requests can be:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Approved:</strong> Request approved to proceed (can be converted to project)</li>
    <li><strong>Deferred:</strong> Request deferred to a future triage meeting</li>
    <li><strong>Rejected:</strong> Request rejected with reasons</li>
    <li><strong>Requires more information:</strong> Request sent back for additional details</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="prioritisation">Prioritisation and scoring</h2>

<p>Demand requests are prioritised and scored to help allocate resources to the most important work.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing prioritisation</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Demand management → Prioritisation</strong></li>
    <li>Filter by tier and portfolio</li>
    <li>View all requests with their prioritisation scores</li>
    <li>Sort by score to see highest priority items</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Scoring a request</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Open a demand request</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Score request"</strong></li>
    <li>Complete the scoring form with:
        <ul>
            <li>Strategic alignment score</li>
            <li>Impact score</li>
            <li>Feasibility score</li>
            <li>Resource availability score</li>
            <li>Other scoring criteria</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save the score</li>
    <li>The prioritisation score is calculated and displayed</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Predicted risk level</h3>

<p>The predicted risk level is automatically calculated from the risk types linked to the demand request:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Risk types have severity levels (Low, Medium, High)</li>
    <li>The highest severity from linked risk types determines predicted risk level</li>
    <li>If no risk types are linked, the "Risk if not delivered" field is used</li>
    <li>Predicted risk level influences prioritisation</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="reporting">Demand reporting</h2>

<p>Comprehensive reporting on demand requests provides insights into demand patterns, prioritisation, and resource allocation.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Demand request reports</h3>

<p>View reports on demand requests:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>By status:</strong> View requests by current status</li>
    <li><strong>By portfolio:</strong> Group requests by portfolio</li>
    <li><strong>By tier:</strong> View requests by governance tier</li>
    <li><strong>By priority:</strong> See highest priority requests</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Charts and trends showing demand patterns</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using demand reports</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Demand management → Reporting</strong></li>
    <li>Apply filters to focus on specific criteria</li>
    <li>View analytics and charts</li>
    <li>Export reports to Excel, PDF, or CSV</li>
    <li>Use reports for portfolio planning and resource allocation</li>
</ol>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="conversion">Converting to projects</h2>

<p>Approved demand requests can be converted into projects for delivery tracking.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Converting a request</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Open an approved demand request</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Convert to project"</strong></li>
    <li>Review the data mapping from request to project</li>
    <li>Confirm the conversion</li>
    <li>The project is created with data populated from the demand request</li>
    <li>The project is linked to the original demand request</li>
    <li>The demand request status is updated to reflect conversion</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> Converting a demand request to a project ensures continuity from request to delivery. The project retains a link to the original request for traceability.</p>
</div>

